### Bluetooth_Fix
# Precaution
!! first use reload cmd and check then only use remove cmd  if reload doesn't work
$ sudo modprobe btusb
$ sudo rmmod btusb


$ sudo rmmod btusb

explanation:-
rmmod stands for remove module.
This removes/unloads the btusb driver from the kernel.

$ sudo modprobe btusb

explanation:-
modprobe is used to load a kernel module.
btusb is the Bluetooth USB driver module in Linux.
So this command activates/loads the Bluetooth driver into the Linux kernel.

$ sudo rmmod btusb
$ sudo modprobe btusb
This unloads and reloads the Bluetooth kernel module ‚Üí fixing many Bluetooth problems.

It works similar to ‚Äúrestart Bluetooth service‚Äù but at a deeper, kernel level.

üö® Important Notes

Removing some modules can temporarily disable related hardware.
Module removal may fail if something is using it (you‚Äôll get an error like ‚ÄúModule in use‚Äù).
Use with care, because kernel modules interact directly with hardware.



